    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SvrDoubleOneDecimalPlaceConvertor

    public class SvrDoubleConverter
extends AbstractConverter
    A converter for the SVR_DOUBLE domain. The format may contain optional locale-specific grouping separators and an optional locale-specific decimal point character. The generic format must use a period character as the decimal point when used and may optionally use commas as thousands separators. Values representing infinity or that are not a number ("NaN") will not be accepted. The absolute magnitude of the maximum and minimum values is imposed by the java.lang.Double class.

      • getDomainClass

        public java.lang.Class<?> getDomainClass()

        Gets the class that is used for the native Java representation of data in this domain. The converter's format should be able to format instances of this class and the parse method should return instances of this class.

        The client infrastructure will use this class to ensure that the converter methods are not passed an object of an incompatible type by checking this class in the implementation of the acceptData(Object) method inherited from the AbstractConverter base class.

        Returns:
        The java.lang.Double class.
